<!--How to Give Section Start-->
<section class="about-three how-to-give-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="about-three__left">
                    <div class="section-title text-left">
                        <span class="section-title__tagline editable">Community Foundation of Teton Valley</span>
                        <h2 class="section-title__title editable">How to Give Through the Tin Cup Challenge</h2>
                    </div>
                    <p class="about-three__text-1 editable">2025 Giving Period is June 13 — July 25.<br>There are two ways to give during the Tin Cup Challenge. Community Donors make a single designated gift, with their chosen amounts allocated to specific nonprofits they wish to support. Challengers and Friends of the Challenge give undesignated funds that help partially match those gifts—boosting the impact for every participating organization. It's a powerful way to come together and make local giving go even further.<br>What is a Tin Cup Donor?<br>One in three households in Teton Valley give through the Tin Cup Challenge—it's a true community effort. Donations come in all sizes, from all over the valley, united by a shared commitment to giving back. When you give during the Tin Cup Giving Period, your designated gifts are boosted by additional funding from Challengers and Friends of the Challenge through a partial match grant.<br>It's easy to give: just pick your favorite nonprofits, decide how much you want to give to each, and make one tax-deductible donation to the Community Foundation. Every gift counts and adds up to something big for our community.</p>
                    <a href="/nonprofits/" class="thm-btn about-three__btn editable">View All Nonprofits</a>
                </div>
            </div>
